label.value: increased vegetative cell population growth on lactate carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is increased relative to normal in a medium containing lactate as the carbon source.

label.value: decreased pre-mRNA level during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of pre-mRNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to heat is lower than normal. Total pre-mRNA or a specific pre-mRNA may be affected.

label.value: resistance to Rho GTPase inhibitor O1

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of GTPase inhibitor O1 than normal.

label.value: abnormal DNA N-glycosylase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of DNA N-glycosylase activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased DNA N-glycosylase activity

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of DNA N-glycosylase activity is increased.

label.value: abnormal mitotic S/G2 phase transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a cell does not execute a mitotic S/G2 cell cycle phase transition normally.

label.value: increased histone H3-K56 acetylation in transcribed regions during mitotic G2/M phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed during the G2/M phase of the mitotic cell cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 56 of histone H3 in regions of the genome that are actively transcribed occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K20 monomethylation in transcribed regions during mitotic G2/M phase

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the G2/M phase of the mitotic cycle in which monomethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 in regions of the genome that are actively transcribed occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: normal histone H3-K56 acetylation during mitotic G2/M phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed during the G2/M phase of the mitotic cell cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 56 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H4-K20 monomethylation during mitotic G2/M phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed during the G2/M phase of the mitotic cell cycle in which monomethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H4-K20 trimethylation during mitotic G2/M phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed during the G2/M phase of the mitotic cell cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased histone H4-K20 trimethylation during mitotic G2/M phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed during the G2/M phase of the mitotic cell cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is decreased.

label.value: increased cellular phosphate (Pi) level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphate (Pi) measured in a cell (total or free) is higher than normal.

label.value: increased total cellular phosphate (Pi) level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of phosphate (Pi) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased free cellular phosphate (Pi) level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of free phosphate (Pi) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: abnormal phosphate export

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the export of phosphate ions (Pi) out of a cell is abnormal.

label.value: sensitive to phosphate (Pi)

definition.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to phosphate (Pi). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of phosphate that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal replication fork arrest at MPS1 barrier

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork arrest at the MPS1 barrier located in the mating-type region is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild-type).

label.value: increased lactate dehydrogenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of lactate dehydrogenase activity is increased.

label.value: microtubule bundles present in increased numbers during mitotic M phase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which cells contain more microtubule bundles than normal during mitotic M-phase.

label.value: microtubule bundles present in normal numbers

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which cells contain a normal number of microtubule bundles.

label.value: normal protein localization to cytoplasmic puncta

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein is localized to discrete regions in the cytoplasm, visible as foci or dots by microscopy, to the same extent as observed in normal (wild type) cells.

label.value: abolished nuclear RNA-directed RNA polymerase complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the assembly of the nuclear RNA-directed RNA polymerase complex is abolished.

label.value: normal siRNA loading onto RITS complex

value.value: An RNA localization phenotype where the loading of siRNAs onto the RITs complex is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal glycerophospholipid level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of glycerophospholipid measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: increased total cellular polyphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of polyphosphate measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased free cellular polyphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of free polyphosphate measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased total cellular polyphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of polyphosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased free cellular polyphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of free polyphosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: abnormal nuclear morphology during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the size, shape, or structure of the nucleus is abnormal during the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: abnormal nuclear morphology during sporulation

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the size, shape, or structure of the nucleus is abnormal during sporulation.

label.value: abolished protein localization to prospore wall

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein does not localize to, and is therefore absent from the prospore wall.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at gene promoter region

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at one or more specific promoter elements is normal  (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during vegetative growth.

label.value: normal cenH-derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA transcribed from cenH measured in a cell is normal. cenH is a region located between mat2-P and mat3-M that is homologous to centromeric repeats, and that produces non-coding RNAs and small interfering RNAs.

label.value: decreased subtelomeric heterochromatin RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA derived from subtelomeric heterochromatin regions is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

label.value: decreased LTR-derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any RNA transcribed from long terminal repeat elements (LTRs) measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at protein coding gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at one or more protein-coding genes is decreased.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at protein coding gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at one or more protein-coding genes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased cenH-derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA transcribed from cenH measured in a cell is lower than normal. cenH is a region located between mat2-P and mat3-M that is homologous to centromeric repeats, and that produces non-coding RNAs and small interfering RNAs.

label.value: normal LTR-derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any RNA transcribed from long terminal repeat elements (LTRs) measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal telomere repeat region derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of telomere repeat derived RNA measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 acetylation at protein coding gene during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions containing protein-coding genes.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K4 acetylation at protein coding gene during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal in regions containing protein-coding genes.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K4 acetylation at LTR during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal at long terminal repeat (LTR) regions.

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 acetylation at LTR during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal at long terminal repeat (LTR) regions.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell surface

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell surface is decreased. The cell surface refers to the external part of the cell wall and/or plasma membrane.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell surface with increased localization to endosomal structures

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell surface is decreased, and the localizatiion to the endosomal structure is increased. The cell surface refers to the external part of the cell wall and/or plasma membrane.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell surface, protein mislocalized to endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell surface is decreased, and the localizatiion to the endoplasmic reticulum is increased. The cell surface refers to the external part of the cell wall and/or plasma membrane.

label.value: decreased cellular mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of annosylinositol phosphorylceramide measured in a cell is lower than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide  measured in a cell is too low to detect.
